s**: Claude Code uses cwd (not repo root) for its project directory, so a session started from a subdirectory stores its transcript under a different project dir name. `attach` searches all project dirs that are subdirectories of the repo root as a fallback.\\n- **Agent-agnostic via `--agent` flag**: Defaults to `claude-code` but supports all registered agents (`gemini`, `opencode`, `cursor`, `copilot-cli`, `factoryai-droid`). The agent interface's `GetSessionDir` / `ResolveSessionFile` / `ReadTranscript` methods handle the per-agent differences.\\n- **No pre-state baseline**: Unlike hook-captured sessions that know the pre-session untracked files, `attach` has no pre-state. It uses `filterToUncommittedFiles` to limit checkpoint contents to files that are actually uncommitted, avoiding noise from already-committed changes.\\n- **Amend prompt with `--force`**: By default, shows the last commit and asks whether to amend it with the checkpoint trailer. `--force` skips the prompt and amends immediately. If the commit already has a trailer, it's a no-op.\\n- **Transcript helpers extracted to `transcript.go`**: `resolveTranscriptPath`, `searchTranscriptInSubdirs`, and related helpers are in a dedicated file to keep `attach.go` focused on the command logic.\\n\\n### Also included (merged from main)\\n\\n- **fix: `trail update` now pushes to remote** â€” `trail update` was only writing locally, unlike `trail create`\\n- **fix: GPG signing in test helpers** â€” tests creating bare repos now disable `commit.gpgsign` consistently\\n- **docs: Copilot CLI added to all documentation**\\n- **deps: bumped posthog-go, golang.org/x/mod, golang.org/x/term**\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] Unit tests for missing session ID, transcript not found, success path, duplicate session detection, and checkpoint ID output\\n- [ ] Manual test: `entire attach <real-session-id>` with Claude Code session\\n- [ ] Manual test: `entire attach --force <session-id>` amends commit without prompting\\n- [ ] M