criptAnalyzer interface {\\n   131â†’\\tAgent\\n   132â†’\\n   133â†’\\t// GetTranscriptPosition returns the current position (length) of a transcript.\\n   134â†’\\t// For JSONL formats (Claude Code), this is the line count.\\n   135â†’\\t// For JSON formats (Gemini CLI), this is the message count.\\n   136â†’\\t// Returns 0 if the file doesn't exist or is empty.\\n   137â†’\\tGetTranscriptPosition(path string) (int, error)\\n   138â†’\\n   139â†’\\t// ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset extracts files modified since a given offset.\\n   140â†’\\t// For JSONL formats (Claude Code), offset is the starting line number.\\n   141â†’\\t// For JSON formats (Gemini CLI), offset is the starting message index.\\n   142â†’\\t// Returns:\\n   143â†’\\t//   - files: list of file paths modified by the agent (from Write/Edit tools)\\n   144â†’\\t//   - currentPosition: the current position (line count or message count)\\n   145â†’\\t//   - error: any error encountered during reading\\n   146â†’\\tExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path string, startOffset int) (files []string, currentPosition int, err error)\\n   147â†’}\\n   148â†’\\n   149â†’// TranscriptPreparer is called before ReadTranscript to handle agent-specific\\n   150â†’// flush/sync requirements (e.g., Claude Code's async transcript writing).\\n   151â†’// The framework calls PrepareTranscript before ReadTranscript if implemented.\\n   152â†’type TranscriptPreparer interface {\\n   153â†’\\tAgent\\n   154â†’\\n   155â†’\\t// PrepareTranscript ensures the transcript is ready to read.\\n   156â†’\\t// For Claude Code, this waits for the async transcript flush to complete.\\n   157â†’\\tPrepareTranscript(ctx context.Context, sessionRef string) error\\n   158â†’}\\n   159â†’\\n   160â†’// TokenCalculator provides token usage calculation for a session.\\n   161â†’// The framework calls this during step save and checkpoint if implemented.\\n   162â†’type TokenCalculator interface {\\n   163â†’\\tAgent\\n   164â†’\\n   165â†’\\t// 